  "headline": "Immune System",
  "description": "The immune system defends against pathogens (bacteria, viruses, fungi, parasites). Two branches: innate (immediate, non-specific — macrophages, neutrophils, complement) and adaptive (delayed, specific — B cells/antibodies, T cells). Vaccination trains adaptive immunity without causing disease.",
